1
00:00:02,819 --> 00:00:07,198
And there’s nothing 
we can do about this.

2
00:00:07,198 --> 00:00:10,310
We have to live
with that somehow.

3
00:00:10,310 --> 00:00:11,264
But …

4
00:00:11,541 --> 00:00:15,670
What for do I know 
that this is like this?

5
00:00:15,670 --> 00:00:18,341
What for?
What do I get from this?

6
00:00:18,341 --> 00:00:22,692
You think that I think 
that I am all this?

7
00:00:22,692 --> 00:00:27,333
[Everybody Wants Happiness]

8
00:00:28,044 --> 00:00:30,266
But where is “me” at all?

9
00:00:30,266 --> 00:00:32,576
Where is “me” in all of this?

10
00:00:34,385 --> 00:00:37,846
Who are you? 
What are you?

11
00:00:37,846 --> 00:00:41,878
Who are you? 
What are you?

12
00:00:42,066 --> 00:00:43,208
Who are you?

13
00:00:43,208 --> 00:00:49,768
The unexamined life 
is not a life worth living.

14
00:00:49,768 --> 00:00:52,197
That’s Socrates’ opinion.

15
00:00:52,197 --> 00:00:56,817
Meaning ātmā‒samīkṣā,
self analysis—

16
00:00:56,817 --> 00:00:59,355
to try and understand:
who I am,

17
00:00:59,355 --> 00:01:02,125
where I’ve come from,
what is my purpose.

18
00:01:02,125 --> 00:01:07,227
We have good and evil 
principles in us.

19
00:01:07,227 --> 00:01:10,118
If we will just live through 
with our good principles

20
00:01:10,118 --> 00:01:11,657
without unwrapping them,

21
00:01:11,657 --> 00:01:13,377
then it’s clear 
we have failed our goal.

22
00:01:13,377 --> 00:01:15,587
But if we only keep them, 
without developing,

23
00:01:15,587 --> 00:01:20,129
then apparently there is no goal 
or purpose of [such] existence.

24
00:01:20,129 --> 00:01:24,510
But to end the life 
on some higher level

25
00:01:24,510 --> 00:01:26,240
than you started from,

26
00:01:26,240 --> 00:01:29,661
that can be the only purpose 
of the human life.

27
00:02:00,023 --> 00:02:02,123
Everyone only thinks 
about what to eat,

28
00:02:02,123 --> 00:02:04,284
what food is good, 
what bad,

29
00:02:04,284 --> 00:02:07,354
what doctor to consult,
what spa to go to.

30
00:02:07,366 --> 00:02:12,547
Everyone is only thinking 
“how” to live,

31
00:02:12,547 --> 00:02:16,256
but “why”—
nobody wants to think.

32
00:02:16,256 --> 00:02:18,254
Everybody wants happiness.

33
00:02:18,254 --> 00:02:22,088
No one can deny 
that they want to be happy.

34
00:02:22,088 --> 00:02:25,533
They want love, affection,

35
00:02:25,533 --> 00:02:29,363
a loving affectionate 
happy relationship.

36
00:02:29,385 --> 00:02:33,465
Atheist, theist, agnostic—
alike.

